sudo apt-get update
sudo apt install docker.io
docker --version

sudo systemctl status docker

sudo systemctl enable --now docker   (First time)

sudo systemctl start docker

sudo systemctl stop docker




Create own container!

Dockerfile:

FROM ubuntu

RUN apt update
RUN yes | apt install git
RUN git --version


COPY file.txt /opt/file





sudo docker build . -t my-test

To tag and upload to Hub


May need while pushing, just give uname &pwd (murthidn & Murthi@19..)
docker login

sudo docker build . -t murthidn/my-test
sudo docker push murthidn/my-test


To get in container
sudo docker run -it my-test bash




